title: PML-N to win over 16 Punjab Assembly seats in by-election: Rana Sana
content:
ISLAMABAD, Jun 27 (APP): Minister for Interior Rana Sanaullah on Monday said the Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz (PML-N) would win by-elections on over 16 seats of the Punjab Assembly.
PML-N Vice President Maryam Nawaz would lead the election campaign of the partyâ€™s candidates, he said while talking to a private news channel.
The minister said the PML-N was not afraid of anyone as the current government led by it was a coalition one, which was taking decisions with consensus.
To a question, Rana Sana said Aslam Bhootani had spoken in the National Assembly in the context of budget. Such speeches in the parliament were a routine matter, he added.
To another question, the minister said Punjab Chief Minister Hamza Shehbaz enjoy the confidence of majority in the Punjab Assembly.
